> Sweeter and thicker than soy sauce, ketjap manis is typically used in Indonesian 
> cuisine. This condiment is a staple in our Asian style recipes and you can 
> find it in anything from larb style salads to fried rice and noodle dishes.

== Noodles ==

Bring a #large saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{0.25%tsp} for the 
noodles.

Halve the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%g}(halved if thick stems) lengthways, then 
cut widthways into thirds.

Trim the @Green Beans{80%g}, then cut into thirds. Peel and grate the 
@Garlic Clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @Lime{1/2}.

When boiling, add the @Egg Noodle Nest{125%g}, green beans and broccoli to the 
water.

Cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop the noodles 
sticking together and to keep the veg vibrant.

== Peanut Sauce ==

Meanwhile, boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the @Boiled Water{200%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for amount) into a 
#measuring jug{}.

Add the @Ketjap Manis{25%g}, @Soy Sauce{15%ml}, @Peanut Butter{30%g} and 
@Sugar{1%tsp} for the sauce (see pantry for amount). Stir well.

Pop the #jug{} to one side.

== Stir-Fry ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Drain the 
@King Prawns{150%g}. 

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns.

Once hot, add the @Coleslaw Mix{120%g} and prawns.

Cook, stirring frequently, until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the @Red Thai Style Paste{50%g} and the garlic. Cook, stirring, for 
~{1%minute} more.

Add the peanut sauce to the pan and stir well until combined.

Stir through the cooked noodles, green beans and broccoli to coat them in the 
sauce, then bring to the boil. Simmer until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once thickened, remove from the heat. Taste and season with @salt{to taste} 
and @pepper{to taste}.

Add a good squeeze of lime juice and a splash of @?water{} if you feel it needs 
it. 

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

== To Serve ==

Share the prawn noodle stir-fry between your #bowls{}.

Crush the @Salted Peanuts{25%g} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}, 
then sprinkle over the top to finish.

Serve with any remaining lime cut into wedges for squeezing over.

Enjoy!